## Column Selection

By default, all columns are shown. The `columns` parameter lets you pick a subset, which is useful
for wide tables where only a few columns are relevant to the discussion.

::: {#2309a294 .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
tbl_preview(
    "../assets/data/students.csv",
    columns=["name", "score", "grade"],
    show_all=True,
)
```

