### Column Width Control

The `max_col_width` parameter caps the pixel width of any single column. Long cell values are
truncated with an ellipsis. The default is 250px.

::: {#5b11048d .cell execution_count=25}
``` {.python .cell-code}
tbl_preview({
    "description": [
        "This is a very long description that would normally extend the column width quite far",
        "Another lengthy entry with lots of detail about the item in question",
        "Short one",
    ],
    "code": ["ABC-001", "DEF-002", "GHI-003"],
}, show_all=True, max_col_width=150)
```

